school website]; accessed 8 May 2015.</ref> The school is named after [[Robert of Newminster|Saint Robert of Newminster]]. Mr Dean Juric is currently [[head teacher]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strobertofnewminster.co.uk/about/headteachers-welcome/|title=Headteacher's Welcome, St Robert of Newminster School|website=www.strobertofnewminster.co.uk}}</ref> and Mr Gregory Moorhouse chair of [[school governor|governors]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strobertofnewminster.co.uk/about/governors/|title=St Robert of Newminster School Governors}}</ref> The school's former executive headteacher, Nick Hurn, was awarded the [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] for services to education.\nSt Robert of Newminster Catholic School is a [[voluntary aided school]] and [[sixth form]] administered by [[Sunderland City Council]] and the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Hexham and Newcastle]]. The school also has a specialism in the humanities. It offers [[General Certificate of Secondary Education|GCSEs]] and [[Business and Technology Education Council|BTECs]].\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n*[[Jordan Pickford]], [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and England<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/jordan-pickford-i-was-always-brave-my-brother-would-get-me-to-dive-on-tarmac-vj52wt22f|accessdate=24 January 2018|title=Jordan Pickford School}}</ref>\n*[[Ethan Robson]], professional footballer for [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]<ref name=\"SAFC\">{{cite web|title=Ethan Robson Profile|url=https://www.safc.com/players/1st-team/ethan-robson|publisher=Sunderland A.F.C.|accessdate=3 October 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Coughlin]], cricketer\n*[[Bridget Phillipson]], [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[Member of Parliament]] (MP) for [[Houghton and Sunderland South (UK Parliament constituency)|Houghton and Sunderland South]] (2010\u2013present)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/local-news/houghton-sunderland-south-constituency-election-8650510|accessdate=5 September 2017|title=Bridget Phillipson: Houghton & Sunderland South constituency election results}}</ref>\n*[[Si King]], [[Hairy Bikers]] member<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/news/tyne-tees/update/2014-07-24/washington-new-town-50-years-on|title=Si King reference|date=24 July 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Thirlwell|Paul Thirwell]], Footballer\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://strobertofnewminster.co.uk/ St Robert of Newminster Catholic School official website]\n\n{{City of Sunderland}}\n{{Schools in Tyne and Wear}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint Robert of Newminster Catholic School}}\n[[Category:Secondary schools in the City of Sunderland]]\n[[Category:Catholic secondary schools in the Diocese of Hexham and Newcastle]]\n[[Category:Voluntary aided schools in England]]\n[[Category:International Baccalaureate schools in England]]\n[[Category:Washington, Tyne and Wear]]\n[[Category:Comprehensive schools in Tyne and Wear]]\n\n{{TyneandWear-school-stub}}\n{{RC-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{One source|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = St. Robert of Newminster Roman Catholic Voluntary Aided School and Sixth Form College\n| image         = \n| image_size          = \n| alt           =\n| caption       = \n| motto         = 'Sic Luceat Lux Vestra' -  'Let your light shine.'\n| established   = \n| closed        = \n| type          = [[Voluntary aided school]]\n| religious_affiliation      = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]]\n| head          = Mr Dean Juric\n| chair_label   = Chair of Governors\n| chair         = Mr Gregory Moorhouse\n| address        = Biddick Lane, Biddick \n| location      = [[Washington, Tyne and Wear|Washington]]\n| city          = [[City of Sunderland]]\n| postcode      = NE38 8AF\n| county        = [[Tyne and Wear]]\n| country       = [[England]]\n| coordinates   = {{coord|54.88815|N|1.5212|W|type:edu_region:GB-SND|display=inline,title}}\n| local_auth